{{Orphan|date=December 2012}}

[[Image:logoweb.jpg|thumb|right|250px|ADAPES logo]]
The '''Asociación de Artistas Plásticos de El Salvador''' (ADAPES) is a prominent arts association in [[El Salvador]]. ADAPES was founded in 1980 by a group of recognized Salvadoran artists. The group's fundamental objective was initially the promotion of plastic arts in El Salvador. Since then, and with the collaboration of private and public institutions, ADAPES has branched out into promoting [[painting]], [[sculpture]] and related visual arts in El Salvador.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.adapes.org/ |title=Web site of the Association of Artists ADAPES |access-date=2018-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080731154051/http://www.adapes.org/ |archive-date=2008-07-31 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

Notable ADAPES members include Marco Valencia, Francisco Zayas, Licry Bicard, Marielos Imery, Romeo Galdamez,Mayra Barraza, Fredis Monge, Hugo Martinez, Carlos Cartagena, Salvador Llort, Mauricio Castillo, Mauricio Linares Aguilar, Evelyn Quinteros, Amber Rose, Tessie Scharaga, Dagoberto Nolasco, Ivan Bran, Armando  Solis, [[Giovanni Gil]], Victor Cartagena, Elisa Archer, Alberto Merino, Marta Eugenia Valle, Ricardo Portillo, Flor Nuila, Antonio Lara, Maria  Kahn, Gilberto Arriaza

